The PLI for each sampling point and entire sampling area were calculated using Eq. (2) and Eq. (3), respectively. Here, PLI represents the MPs load index at a sampling point, and PLIzone refers to the MPs pollution load index for the sampled area. If PLI < 10, the study area is classified as hazard category I; 10 < PLI < 20 indicates hazard category II; 20 < PLI < 30 represents hazard category III; and PLI > 30 indicates hazard category IV (Hossain et al. 2024; Ranjani et al. 2021).2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
